Cook pasta according to package directions. Drain well. Set aside. Meanwhile, in a blender container, combine undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, wine, oregano, and pepper. Cover; blend until smooth. Set aside. In a large skillet, cook ground beef and onion until beef is no longer pink. Drain well. Stir in tomato mixture. Bring to boiling; reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes. Stir in pasta and olives. Spoon the pasta mixture into a 2-quart casserole. Bake, covered, in a 375 degrees F oven for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with mozzarella cheese. Bake, uncovered, about 5 minutes more or until heated through. (Or, chill unbaked casserole, covered, in the refrigerator for up to 24 hours. Bake in a 375 degrees F oven for 45 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes more.)